<title>USA: USA Today expands news staff - NYT.</title>
<headline>USA Today expands news staff - NYT.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-08-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>USA Today has hired more editors and reporters to expand its news coverage and produce more investigative pieces, the New York Times said on Monday.</p>
<p>USA Today will open bureaus in Denver, Atlanta and Boston, according to the Times.</p>
<p>The company had previously only relied on free-lancers in those cities, the paper said.</p>
<p>USA Today is also adding a Life-section reporter to its San Francisco bureau and two reporters to its national staff, the newspaper said.</p>
<p>USA Today is a unit of Gannett Co.</p>
